      { heading: "Catering Options by Package Level", content: "MerrySails offers three levels of yacht catering. The Essential package (€280) includes basic refreshments — Turkish tea, coffee, water, and light snacks. You can bring your own food and drinks at no additional charge, making this the most flexible budget option. The Premium package (€380) adds a curated drink menu (wine, beer, spirits, soft drinks) and a refreshment spread. The VIP package (€680) includes a private chef who prepares a fully customized multi-course meal on board — this is the ultimate dining experience on the Bosphorus. Additional catering packages can be added to any package level, ranging from simple meze platters to elaborate seafood feasts." },
      { heading: "Turkish Meze Spread — Classic Yacht Menu", content: "The meze spread is the most popular yacht catering choice — perfectly suited to the casual, social atmosphere of a Bosphorus cruise. A typical meze selection includes: hummus, acılı ezme (spicy tomato-walnut paste), cacık (yogurt with cucumber), sigara böreği (crispy cheese rolls), yaprak sarma (stuffed vine leaves), patlıcan salatası (smoky eggplant salad), haydari (herb yogurt dip), and fresh bread. The meze format is ideal for yacht dining because it is easy to share, does not require formal table settings, and pairs perfectly with drinks. Add grilled meat or seafood for a more substantial meal. Meze platters serve 8–15 guests and are prepared fresh before the charter." },
      { heading: "Seafood and BBQ Options", content: "For a heartier yacht menu, seafood and BBQ options elevate the experience. The seafood menu includes: grilled sea bass (levrek), shrimp, calamari, and octopus, served with seasonal salad and rice. Fresh fish is sourced from Istanbul's morning markets. The BBQ menu features Turkish-style grilled meats: chicken shish, lamb kebab, köfte (meatballs), and grilled vegetables, served with pilaf and salad. Both menus can be prepared by the crew on the yacht's grill or by a private chef (VIP package). For the most impressive presentation, the VIP private chef creates a tasting menu with multiple courses timed to scenic moments during the cruise." },
      { heading: "Drinks — From Tea to Champagne", content: "The drink selection sets the mood for your charter. Basic (Essential): Turkish tea, coffee, and water. Premium: wine (Turkish reds and whites), beer (Efes, craft options), spirits (rakı, vodka, whisky, gin), soft drinks, juices. VIP: everything in Premium plus champagne (Moët or equivalent), premium spirits, and cocktail service. Turkish rakı — the national spirit — is a classic Bosphorus drink; served with cold water and ice, it turns milky white (earning the nickname 'lion's milk'). For celebrations, champagne towers or custom cocktails can be arranged. Non-alcoholic options are always comprehensive: fresh juices, Turkish ayran (salted yogurt drink), homemade lemonade, and premium teas." },
      { heading: "Special Dietary Requirements", content: "All yacht catering can accommodate dietary needs. Vegetarian menus feature meze platters (naturally veggie-heavy in Turkish cuisine), grilled vegetable kebabs, and Turkish salads. Vegan options include hummus, rice-stuffed vegetables, grilled aubergine, and fresh fruit. Gluten-free guests can enjoy all grilled items and most meze (börek excluded). Halal food is standard — Turkish cuisine is inherently halal. Kosher arrangements can be made with advance notice. Allergies should be communicated when booking — the chef or catering team adjusts the menu accordingly. For custom dietary requirements, the VIP private chef creates a fully personalized menu around your needs." }
